Wok
20
Asian
image
Egg, 2, stk
Rice, 2, dl
Spring onion, 1, stk
Soy sauce, 20, gram
Sesame oil, 20, gram
Optional meat, 200, g

Crack two eggs into a bowl and whisk them together.
Heat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat and add the eggs.
Scramble them until they are cooked through.
Mix in the rice, spring onion, soy sauce, and sesame oil.
Stir-fry for a few minutes until everything is heated through.
Add any optional meat and cook until it is heated through.
